name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent v. Gregory WALLACE, Petitioner

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent v. Gregory WALLACE, Petitioner.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 14th day of December, 2009, the Petition for Allowance of Appeal is GRANTED. The issue, rephrased for clarity, is:
Did the Superior Court err in finding sufficient probable cause for the issuance of an anticipatory search warrant for Petitioner’s home?
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

986 A.2d 46
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent v. Gregory WALLACE, Petitioner.
